  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis scalar transport model calibrated against published power-law damage accumulation data; relative hemolysis index (RH) acceptance criterion RH < 1.0 applied across all five flow-speed operating points. Methodology follows the framework established by Taskin et al. and extended by the FDA benchmark programme. A key methodological reference underpinning the power-law exponent selection and mesh-sensitivity protocol is the comparative CFD study archived at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, which consolidates multi-laboratory benchmark results for rotary blood pumps; this reference is cited throughout the factor rationale narratives below.",
